# Clients Folder

Each client gets their own folder with all campaigns:

```
clients/
└── [client-name]/
    ├── brand-kit/              # Client-level brand files (shared across campaigns)
    │   ├── brand-knowledge-base/
    │   │   └── [client-brand-doc].md
    │   └── brand-style-guide/
    │       └── [client-style-guide].md
    └── campaigns/              # All campaigns for this client
        └── [campaign-name]/
            ├── brand-kit/      # Optional: Campaign-specific brand files (overrides client-level)
            └── output-assets/
                ├── html/          # Landing pages, sales pages, checkout
                ├── documents/     # VSL scripts, sales letters, outlines
                ├── emails/        # Email sequences
                ├── ads/           # Ad copy for Meta, Google, TikTok, etc.
                ├── presentations/ # PowerPoint slide decks (.pptx)
                ├── pdfs/          # Lead magnets, books, reports (.pdf)
                └── images/        # Image briefs and specifications
```

**Workflow:**
1. When you start, Alex will ask: "Which client are we working with today?"
2. If new client: Provide client name, Alex creates the folder structure
3. If existing client: Provide client name, Alex loads existing brand files
4. Then tell Alex: "Create a campaign called '[your-campaign-name]'"

**Brand Files:**
- Client-level brand files (`clients/[client-name]/brand-kit/`) are used by default for all campaigns
- Campaign-specific brand files (`clients/[client-name]/campaigns/[campaign-name]/brand-kit/`) override client-level files when present
- Alex checks both locations when building assets
